The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | New info panel chief
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      New info panel chief
                            
	New Delhi, Sept. 29 (PTI): Information commissioner A.N. Tiwari was named the new head of transparency panel CIC after the five-year term of the incumbent, Wajahat Habibullah, ended today.        
	President Pratibha Patil gave her assent to the nomination of Tiwari, a 1969-batch IAS officer who is also a former secretary of the department of personnel and training, official sources said.        
	Tiwari, who joined the Central Information Commission on December 26, 2005, will have a three-month tenure as his five-year term ends in December this year.        
	According to the RTI Act, where the information commissioner is appointed as the chief information commissioner, his term of office shall not be more than five years in aggregate as the information commissioner and the chief information commissioner.        
	In a path-breaking decision, Tiwari, as information commissioner, had brought income tax returns of political parties under public scrutiny.        
	The chief information commissioner is chosen by a committee comprising the Prime Minister, the leader of the Opposition and a Union cabinet minister.                                                                                                                                                           
